event_name: Sacred Journey and Play at Taum Sauk Mountain - MO
post_content:
Taum Sauk is one of Earth's oldest Apus and we are blessed to have it in our geographical backyard. Everyone is invited to join our beloved brother Gary Langston to feed the Apachetta at Taum Sauk Mountain Saturday meeting between 10:00-10:30 and departing at 10:45 from the Interpretive Center parking lot at Johnson Shut-ins.
(http://mostateparks.com/park/johnsons-shut-ins-state-park). Afterwards we will play and partake of the beautiful and world unique formations in the area.

Several of our brothers and sisters are going to be going on their pilgrimage/paqowachu during this weekend. As always lets supportive by respecting their sacred journey by being mindful of our family in solitude.

 Make arrangements for lodging on you own by calling Johnson's Shut-Ins State Park----573-546-2450. You can also make online reservations at
http://mostateparks.com/page/54942/camping-reservation-system

 Camp Fees range from $13 for Basic Campsites to $75 for cabins per day. There are walk-in sites
